  "text": "GFP/GFP mice from both lines showed severe growth retardation relative to littermate controls by E11.5, as well as posterior patterning and body axis rotation defects ( Figure 1D ). In both lines, Sox17 GFP/GFP mice were observed in expected ratios through E12.5 but died by E13.5 ( Figure 1E ). This phenotype is consistent with that of independently targeted Sox17-deficient mice that also died embryonically with growth retardation and posterior patterning defects [CITATION_1] .",
